(14) One member to represent the La. Center for Law and Civic Education, appointed by
the president of its board of directors.
(15) One member to represent the La. Chapter of the National Association for the
Advancement of Colored People, appointed by the president of the La. Chapter of
the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People.
(16) The chairman of the Volunteer Louisiana Commission, or his designee.
(17) One member to represent the La. District Judges Association, appointed by the
president of its board of directors.
(18) The chief justice of the La. Supreme Court or his designee.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law additionally provides for the following members:
(1) One state coordinator of the La. Legislators Back to School Program, to represent the
Senate program, appointed by the president of the Senate.
(2) One state coordinator of the La. Legislators Back to School Program, to represent the
House of Representatives program, appointed by the speaker of the House of
Representatives.
Proposed law provides instead for one state coordinator of the La. Legislators Back to
School Program as a member who is appointed jointly by the president and the speaker.
Present law additionally provides that the executive director of the Council for a Better
Louisiana is a member. Proposed law changes the name of the entity to Leaders for a Better
Louisiana and authorizes the executive director to designate a member. Otherwise retains
present law.
Present law further provides for the following members:
(1) The state coordinator of Project Citizen.
(2) The executive director of the Public Affairs Research Council.
Proposed law authorizes the state coordinator and executive director to designate a member.
Otherwise retains present law.
Present law provides for the following additional members:
(1) One member to represent the La. Association of Non-Profit Organizations, appointed
by the chairman of the La. Association of Non-Profit Organizations.
(2) Any additional member who has expertise in civic education or civic involvement,
as may be designated by three-fourths of the commission members present and
voting. Such member shall serve at the pleasure of the commission.
Proposed law repeals present law.
Proposed law provides that 10 members of the commission shall constitute a quorum for the
transaction of business, and that all official action of the commission shall require the
favorable vote of a majority of those members present and voting.
(Amends R.S. 24:972(A)(11)-(22); Adds R.S. 24:972(F); Repeals R.S. 24:972(A)(23)-(25))
